We ordered takeout via Uber Eats. Our experience of delivery from all companies and restaurants have had ups and downs. This was an amazing experience!  Several reviews stated they felt that portions were getting smaller with time. That's not our driving force behind our selections, but man were we surprised! Our sub $40 order yielded us 7.4lbs. Those are Chipotle numbers! And the quality was way better than expected.  The chicken had mixed reviews. Some thought that the chicken was dry which meant it was on the rotisserie for too long. I feel bad for those that didn't get the chicken we received. It was amazingly juicy and possibly a hint of huaycatay. So damn good.  The plantains were perfectly carmelized and texture was perfectly on the middle. Not too soft thankfully. I still have my teeth. The black beans were amazing with the onion salad and a must have combo. Yuca and fries with the medium sauce, I had to get in my comfy pants! I couldn't stop eating them.  And then there was the Tres Leches. If you don't do this you've don't it all wrong. World class texture even for delivered food in with hot packages! How?  So, yes we will be eating leftovers all weekend. There was just way too much food! Well except dessert. We unabashedly crushed all the cake. Don't care. Loved it. We will definitely be ordering regularly.  Thank you District Rico for an amazing experience on a much needed date night at home.
